               <p>PETER DAVIE. I am a <rs id="t18300415-341-viclabel1844" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-341-victim2820 t18300415-341-viclabel1844"></join>. On the 21st of February, about one o'clock, I was coming out of <placeName id="t18300415-341-crimeloc1845">Christchurch, Newgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-341-crimeloc1845" type="placeName" value="Christchurch, Newgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-341-crimeloc1845" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-341-off1842 t18300415-341-crimeloc1845"></join>, the officer called my attention to the prisoner, and I saw my handkerchief found on him - I had not felt it taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-341-person2821">
                  JOHN 
                  LACY HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18300415-341-person2821" type="surname" value="LACY HAWKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-341-person2821" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-341-person2821" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a marshalsman. The Lord Mayor and Sheriffs were attending a charity sermon at Christchurch; the congregation were coming out - I heard some complaint in the church; the prisoner was in the porch, coming out - I looked over, and saw him stooping his head down, and walking softly; he had a leather cap on - I could not see his hands; his cap was moving - I could not account for it; I took hold of both his arms, and said, "How did you come to church?" he said, "Because I heard the Lord Mayor was coming;" I said, "Where do you live?" he said over the water - I took him to the lodge of Christ's-hospital, searched him, and found two handkerchiefs on him; while I was questioning him the prosecutor came up, and claimed one.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence (written.) I went to Christ's-hospital to hear Divine service; when the service was over, they came out in a great confusion - coming along the church-way out I saw a handkerchief lay under my feet; I of couse picked it up, and put it into my pocket, with a full view, after I got out of the church, to make it known to some person, for advice what to do with it, but some person who saw me pick up the said handkerchief, no doubt, gave information to the beadle.</p>
               <p>MR. DAVIE. My handkerchief was in my right-hand pocket; it could not have dropped out.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-341-verdict1846" type="verdictDescription">
